Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da yin zanga-zanga da kuma yin zanga-zanga
Bayan mako guda da jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani sanarwa a cikin jaridar Amirka guda hudu da ta tattauna amfanin da ake samu a harkokin kasuwanci tsakanin kasashen biyu, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafofin watsa labarai na Amirka don yada wannan sanarwa.
A ranar Laraba, shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana game da wani talla da jaridar kasar Sin Des Moines Register ta yi a cikin jaridar da ta fi kowa samun talla a jihar Iowa, bayan da ya zargi kasar Sin da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba.
Trump ya yi ikirarin cewa Beijing na son shiga cikin kasuwar zaben Amurka, wanda jami'an Amurka suka bayyana wa Reuters a matsayin sabon mataki a cikin fadada yakin neman zaben Washington na yin amfani da matsin lamba daga kasar Sin.
Ko da yake yana da kyau gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje su yi tallatawa don su tilasta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington suna cikin yaƙi na kasuwanci da ke ci gaba, da sabon haraji a kan kayayyakin da suke shigowa daga ƙasashe.
Masana a kasar Sin da Amurka sun ce an yi amfani da kuɗin fansa na kasar Sin a farkon yakin kasuwanci don cutar da 'yan gudun hijira a jihohin Iowa, wadanda suka yi wa Trump ja-gora a jam'iyyar Republican.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa na dogon lokaci, yayin da jihar ke fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni lahani.
Branstad ya ce a cikin wani rahoto da ya wallafa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register na Lahadi, "China tana ƙara tsananta wa 'yan ta'adda ta wajen wallafa labarai masu ban tsoro a cikin jaridarmu ta 'yanci".
